Description: Bruegel: View of Naples. The type to be found in cartography, also after Bruegel, e.g. Frontispiece of Willem BARENT[= Barentsz], Caertboeck 1595 (in Nederlandsch Historische Scheepvaart Museum, A'dam) repr. in H.P. BAARD, Willem van de Velde de Oude, Willem van de Velde de Jonge, Amsterdam, Palet serie), 1942, p. 4, cf. also Hendrick Cornelisz. Vroom, Return from the 2nd expedition to East India (9 July 1599) (A'dam, Rijksmuseum, repr. ibidem, n° 7); [kantlijn] Also in the English 'Platts' see [Erna] Auerbach on Volpe in Burl.Mag.[92, (1950)].
